1.00	Timothy_Gallagher	Timothy Gallagher	Timothy M. Gallagher is the Boston-based author of 6 bestselling books on the theology and spirituality of Ignatius of Loyola. A former head (provincial) of the Catholic religious community Oblates of the Virgin Mary, Gallagher earned his doctorate from The Pontifical Gregorian University, became a spiritual director and retreat leader, and since 2003 has written a series of books on core topics in Ignatian spirituality, including contemplation and meditation. The Examen Prayer, honored by the Catholic Press Association, was the first to appear on the national Catholic bestseller list.The Discernment of Spirits was later made into a 26-part CatholicTV series.	
